<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910308-0120</DOCNO><DOCID>910308-0120.</DOCID><HL>   General Host Net Falls</HL><DATE>03/08/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   GH</CO><IN>SPECIALTY RETAILERS (OTS)EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><LP>   STAMFORD, Conn. -- General Host Corp., citing weak salesin January because of the Persian Gulf war, said fiscalfourth-quarter net income fell nearly 32% to $3.8 million, or21 cents a share.   In the year-earlier period, the lawn-and-garden productsretailer earned $5.5 million, or 29 cents a share. Sales inthe latest period, ended Jan. 27, rose 3% to $136.3 millionfrom $132.3 million.</LP><TEXT>   The company said operating earnings fell short of lastyear's record results mostly because of weak January resultsreflecting consumer concern about the Persian Gulf war.</TEXT></DOC>